This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the detection of blood vessels in fundus images using deep learning techniques. The use of ensemble learning also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning models and the focus on accuracy and performance suggest that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of neural networks also suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of image processing techniques and the focus on medical imaging suggest that it may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
